laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis; Small wedge-shaped area of heterogeneous hyperenhancement of the liver in segment VIII likely due to perfusion abnormalities; Grossly unchanged infiltrative tumor in right hepatic lobe; Stable 1.9 cm left hepatic cyst; Mild residual intrahepatic biliary dilatation with pneumobilia; Partially overlapping metallic common bile duct stents; Debris within common bile duct stent; Severe right hydronephrosis with abrupt taper at UPJ; Redemonstration of complex solid and cystic mass in pelvis measuring 10.3 x 8.7 x 8.0 cm; 1.1 cm left periaortic lymph node measuring similar to prior; Trace anterolisthesis of L4 on L5 and slight multilevel degenerative changes.
